This class is likely used to collect additional performance metrics, such as CPU usage and RAM usage, during a benchmark test using the Java Microbenchmark Harness (JMH) framework.\",\"/src/main/java/project/Matrix.java\":\"This file contains a single class, `Matrix`, which represents a matrix and provides methods for multiplying two matrices and accessing the result.\\n\\n`Matrix`: A class that represents a matrix and provides methods for multiplying two matrices and accessing the result.\\n\\n`Matrix(Random rnd, int size)`: A constructor that initializes the matrices `a` and `b` with random values and sets the size of the matrices.\\n\\n`multiply()`: A method that performs the matrix multiplication of `a` and `b` and stores the result in `c`.\\n\\n`peek()`: A method that returns the value of the first element (0,0) of the resulting matrix `c`.\",\"/src/main/java/project/Benchmarking.java\":\"This file contains a single class `Benchmarking` that performs a benchmark test for matrix multiplication using the JMH (Java Microbenchmark Harness) framework.\\n\\n`Benchmarking`: A class that sets up and runs a benchmark for matrix multiplication, measuring CPU usage and memory consumption.\\n\\n`setupTrial()`: Initializes the matrix for the benchmark.\\n\\n`setupIteration()`: Records the start time and CPU time before each benchmark iteration.\\n\\n`multiply(Blackhole)`: Performs the matrix multiplication and consumes the result.\\n\\n`tearDownInvocation(ExtraMetrics)`: Records the CPU usage and memory consumption after each benchmark iteration.\\n\\nThe file also includes some comments that provide instructions for running the benchmark.\"}"}
